{
  "stem": "12462.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So you had this, what we would call, a real conflict of interest, actually here.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the way it was used in-- in Germany, it just made the industry the servant of the-- of the Nazi Reich.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We also charged the-- the defendants in the Krupp case with aggressive war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But in both of these cases, the tribunals did not find the-- any defendant guilty of aggressive war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In each of the cases, there were some findings [CLEARS THROAT] of guilt for slave labor and for spoliation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Were their convictions in all of the cases in which you participated in the subsequent proceedings?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think a third of the defendants in the IG Farben case, or maybe nine altogether, were found guilty on one count or another, on spoiliation or on slave labor, the use of concentration camp labor.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But over half the defendants in the Farben case were found not guilty on any count.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the Flick case, I don't remember the exact figures, but I would think, of about seven or eight defendants, all, except perhaps one, were found guilty of slave labor or spoliation.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What were the range of sentences your convicted defendants received in the subsequent proceedings?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were, in the-- in the medical case and in the Einsatzgruppen case, I believe, some of the defendants were sentenced to-- to death.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the medical case, those sentenced to death, that was-- they-- those sentences were carried out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in the later cases, there was appeals to the clemency-- to the military governor, McCloy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he appointed a commission, which didn't consult the representatives of the prosecution or any of the former prosecutors, but what they thought.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a lot of them said there's variation in these sentences.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
